node.text:
Adorable mask from @_simply_bea_!!

Reposted from @_simply_bea_ 🐯 Roar! Today is International Tiger Day so I thought it would be fun for the kids and I to craft a cardboard Tiger. 😉

I started with cutting out the pieces for our cardboard Tiger face, I wanted a layered effect so the kids can paint the pieces individually using a sponge roller and washable paints. They also helped in gluing the pieces together and I fished up with the finer details! ☺️

Whilst our project was drying, we watched 2 documentaries on YouTube, one in German to for some extra language learning. 😁

Did you know that Tigers are the largest in the Big Cat family and they actually like water unlike most cats? 😉

Our Tiger is joining in on a few play prompts this week:

What a cute idea from @iracreativeengine!!
Reposted from @iracreativeengine 🌴🚙CAMPER VAN - let's go on holiday 🎊
PRETEND PLAY 

It's been 2 years where we are in house and  travelling mode is off 🛑, so made this cute Camp Van for ira to enjoy travelling in a house with her fav toys 😁

Ira helped me in  painting and fixing  the wheels

🚙How we made

⭐Instead of it looking complex was very easy to make 
Swipe to see only with  4  pieces of cardboard we made this beauty 

1. shaped and cut
2.  then paint them 
3 Used straw for the fixing wheel and window stopper.
4. Use playdough box lid as wheel 😁

We made one coconut  tree and bunting to give it a full  holiday feel 🤩🤩

Happy ira is the outcome 😁so all her animals are enjoying the holidays along with her 🤩...

Do check my friends Aisha @toontots and Aparna @activeyuvi_consiousmom awesome vehicle plays 

Completely inspired: @blog.estefi.machado ( love her cardboard creations )

node.text:
Such a great forest from @minimadthings!!

Reposted from @minimadthings Cardboard forest...
I made this cute cardboard forest for a guest blog post for the fab @theartfulparent a little while back. Head to their website to find out more.

This week for #makecreateplay our guest host @acorns.and.aprons asked us to get crafty with TREES. To play along TAG your TREE theme crafts with #MAKECREATEPLAY and FOLLOW hosts @littlegingerstudio @minimadthings and this weeks guest host @acorns.and.aprons  I will be sharing your creations in my stories all week and Angela will pick their faves on Sunday. Each Monday we will announce a new theme and share the winners from the previous week. Don’t forget to TAG all the hosts in your posts too, that way we won’t miss your cool creations!

The concept behind #MAKECREATEPLAY is that you and your little ones create activities or crafts that they can then play with. 
In a world of over-consumption we would like to encourage people to use recycling, found natural objects, simple household materials and craft supplies in creative ways to create play.

node.text:
What a beautiful owl from @unlocking.fun!!

Reposted from @unlocking.fun ***Clover flower barn owl*** by Sam.

I thought it would be nice to make a feature of the humble clover flower, which is so abundant at this time of year. We really enjoyed collecting it up and adding it to our barn owl picture, to add texture. I’ve found that this flower dries out nicely too.

A lovely idea from @playwithmamma!

Reposted from @playwithmamma 🏖 The sea inside the jar🏝

When I think of summer I can think of sea, colors and ice cream, of which I am really greedy!!!
I'm so honored and super excited to be joining @minimadthings and @littlegingerstudio for this week of #makecreateplay with COLOURS!!!Share all your colorful post using the hastag #makecreateplay, i'll be sharing on my stories and picking my favourites at the end of the week. Enjoy with #makecreateplay!

🏝Il mare dentro al barattolo🏖

Quando penso all'estate mi vengono in mente mare, colori e gelati, di cui sono davvero golosa!!!
Sono così onorata e super entusiasta di unirmi a @minimadthings e @littlegingerstudio questa settimana di #makecreateplay con COLOURS!!! Condividi tutti i tuoi post colorati utilizzando l'hastag #makecreateplay, li condividerò nelle mie storie e sceglierò i miei preferiti alla fine della settimana. Divertiti con #makecreateplay
